messages.content: ComfyUI-SDXL-EmptyLatentImage is an extension node for ComfyUI that allows users to select a resolution from pre-defined json files and output a Latent Image.
How does ComfyUI-SDXL-EmptyLatentImage retrieve a list of resolutions?
The node retrieves a list of resolutions from a json file saved in a specific format and displays them in a dropdown list on the node's interface.
Can I select a resolution manually in ComfyUI-SDXL-EmptyLatentImage?
No, you cannot select a resolution manually. You must choose from the pre-defined resolutions in the dropdown list provided by the node.
What is the aspect ratio displayed in the dropdown list?
The aspect ratio displayed in the dropdown list is calculated as `width / height` of the selected resolution.
Does ComfyUI-SDXL-EmptyLatentImage come with pre-defined resolution sets?
Yes, the [sdxl_resolution_set.json](sdxl_resolution_set.json) file is provided with a set of resolutions considered optimal for training in SDXL.
How can I load a custom resolution file?
During node initialization, you can load a .json file with custom resolution settings. A sample resolution set for SD1.5 is provided in [sd_resolution_set.json](sd_resolution_set.json).

To install, navigate to the 'custom_nodes' folder where ComfyUI is installed, then use 'git clone' to clone the [ComfyUI-SDXL-EmptyLatentImage](https://github.com/shingo1228/ComfyUI-SDXL-EmptyLatentImage) repository as per the instructions.
